reproduction rate, percentage of mictic offspring of B. calyciflorus (P < 0.05), 
Cd2+ concentration had significant effects on the generation time and the 
percentage of mictic offspring (P < 0.05), and the interaction of S. obliquus 
density and Cd2+ concentration had significant effects on the percentage of 
mictic offspring (P < 0.01). Among all the studied parameters, the generation 
time and the percentage of mictic offspring were more sensitive to Cd2+ 
pollution under the algal densities of 1.0 x 10(6) and 3.0 x 10(6) cells x 
ml(-1), with the latter being the most sensitive.

